{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-tsx","path":"/2021/06/neovim.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"00b1a556-e625-5bc4-b345-a0199da9133a","html":"<p>I have switched VSCode entirely to Vim for six months. VSCode is a great editor and very powerful, but I need something that makes me more productive. I used to learn how to use Vim many times since I was at university, but I gave up.\nBut this time was different,  I made it more serious, and I thought I had completed two goals: use 100% Vim and the speed of using Vim on par with the time of using VSCode.</p>\n<figure class=\"float-right\" style=\"width: 600px\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/a331c/vim-learning-curve-duyet.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/e93cc/vim-learning-curve-duyet.webp 300w,\n/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/b0544/vim-learning-curve-duyet.webp 600w,\n/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/8d2ea/vim-learning-curve-duyet.webp 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/eed55/vim-learning-curve-duyet.png 300w,\n/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/7491f/vim-learning-curve-duyet.png 600w,\n/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/a331c/vim-learning-curve-duyet.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" type=\"image/png\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/4a56e56d961cd1d779db156b22a84d5a/a331c/vim-learning-curve-duyet.png\" alt=\"vim learning curve duyet\" title=\"vim learning curve duyet\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 446px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/0417c/using-vim.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 77%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/e93cc/using-vim.webp 300w,\n/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/7bab6/using-vim.webp 446w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/eed55/using-vim.png 300w,\n/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/0417c/using-vim.png 446w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px\" type=\"image/png\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/37f99fb05d38986a2938ced46ce47548/0417c/using-vim.png\" alt=\"using vim\" title=\"using vim\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</figure>\n<p>This week I give it a chance to migrate to NeoVim. There are many reasons for me to make a decision:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Programs can interact with neovim using a remote API.</li>\n<li>Strong default settings.</li>\n<li>It can be running in many GUIs, IDEs, web browsers.</li>\n<li>It fixes every issue I have with Vim.</li>\n<li>Executing jobs/tasks asynchronously to improve performance.</li>\n<li>The NeoVim config and plugin are fully compatible with Vim.</li>\n<li>A nice website :)</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"downloading\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#downloading\" aria-label=\"downloading permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Downloading</h1>\n<p>NeoVim can be installed in many ways, according to the Wiki: <a href=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/Installing-Neovim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/Installing-Neovim</a>.</p>\n<p>I’m using Homebrew to install on my Mac:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> neovim</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"neovim-config\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#neovim-config\" aria-label=\"neovim config permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NeoVim config</h1>\n<p>And you will not need to install the plugins or configure everything again.\nIf you wish to migrate your existing Vim configuration to NeoVim, simply copy your ~/.vimrc to ~/.config/nvim/init.vim.</p>\n<p>In this case, I want to share the old Vim config with the NeoVim, I simply created a file <code class=\"language-text\">~/.config/nvim/init.vim</code> and with the content below to route NeoVim config to my previous vim setup:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"vim\"><pre class=\"language-vim\"><code class=\"language-vim\"><span class=\"token keyword\">set</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">runtimepath</span>^<span class=\"token operator\">=~</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">.</span><span class=\"token keyword\">vim</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">runtimepath</span><span class=\"token operator\">+=</span>~<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">.</span><span class=\"token keyword\">vim</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>after\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> &amp;packpath <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> &amp;<span class=\"token builtin\">runtimepath</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">source</span> ~<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">.</span>vimrc</code></pre></div>\n<p>NeoVim isn’t entirely compatible with Vim, but almost all plugins work on NeoVim too, with me, all plugins worked fine.</p>\n<p>On the other hands, I’m using this vimrc preset with a ton of useful plugins, color schemes, and configurations: <a href=\"https://github.com/amix/vimrc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/amix/vimrc</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/eddf6/neovim.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/e93cc/neovim.webp 300w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/b0544/neovim.webp 600w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/68fc1/neovim.webp 1200w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/a2303/neovim.webp 1800w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/4293a/neovim.webp 2400w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/f6b9b/neovim.webp 2442w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/eed55/neovim.png 300w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/7491f/neovim.png 600w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/8537d/neovim.png 1200w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/d2cc9/neovim.png 1800w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/00711/neovim.png 2400w,\n/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/eddf6/neovim.png 2442w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/15cbfe4ed6204cec2c50107d14aac213/8537d/neovim.png\"\n            alt=\"neovim\"\n            title=\"neovim\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/eddf6/neovim-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/e93cc/neovim-2.webp 300w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/b0544/neovim-2.webp 600w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/68fc1/neovim-2.webp 1200w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/a2303/neovim-2.webp 1800w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/4293a/neovim-2.webp 2400w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/f6b9b/neovim-2.webp 2442w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/eed55/neovim-2.png 300w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/7491f/neovim-2.png 600w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/8537d/neovim-2.png 1200w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/d2cc9/neovim-2.png 1800w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/00711/neovim-2.png 2400w,\n/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/eddf6/neovim-2.png 2442w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/191ade210d669ca0664352e53b26409a/8537d/neovim-2.png\"\n            alt=\"neovim 2\"\n            title=\"neovim 2\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>And the final thoughts, NeoVim has some plugins that take advantage of specific NeoVum features, and you can check it <a href=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/Related-projects\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/2021/06/neovim.html","tagSlugs":["/tag/dev/","/tag/vim/","/tag/code-editor/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-06-15T00:00:00.000+07:00","description":"I migrated to NeoVim, after six month with Vim.","tags":["Dev","Vim","Code Editor"],"title":"Migrating from Vim to NeoVim","fbCommentUrl":"none"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2021/06/neovim.html"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","2672868365","401334301"]}